It was proposed by Robert Floyd in 1959 and independently by Stephen Warshall in 1962.
: Floyd's Algorithm is based on a dynamic programming approach, which builds up solutions to larger subproblems from solutions to smaller subproblems.
Finding the shortest paths in road networks.
It's a fundamental algorithm in graph theory and network analysis.

Floyd's Algorithm provides a robust and efficient solution for finding shortest paths in graphs, making it a valuable tool in various fields including computer networking, transportation, and logistics.

This report will propose an alternative to the Floyd-Warshall algorithm based on iteration (Floyd Warshall Algorithm | DP-16, 2023) while focusing on some recursive approach. In addition, the time performance of both proposals will be compared and discussed as it may seem that the iterative version of the algorithm could be more efficient than the re-cursive version in terms of time performance, particularly when processing big input graphs.
